==Japanese==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[Kanji]]: [[お腹]], [[御腹]] ("stomach" sense only)
*[[Kana]]: [[おなか]]
*[[Romaji]]: [[onaka]]
===Etymology===
[[御-]] ''o-'' ([[honorific]] prefix) + [[中]] ''naka'' "middle"
===Noun===
'''御中'''

# (''originally [[女房詞|nyōbō kotoba]]'') [[abdomen]], [[belly]], [[stomach]]
# (''in [[女房詞|nyōbō kotoba]], the secret language of court ladies'') a [[meal]], especially of [[rice]]
# (''in [[女房詞|nyōbō kotoba]], the secret language of court ladies'') [[cotton]]
# the title of a [[maid]] working in the inner part of a military family's house during the [[Muromachi]] era
